stylometry: Transportation problems are like going from one point to another, the first point would be the origin and the second point would be the destination. An example would be going from a factory to a warehouse.  In a Transshipment problem a location can be both an origin and a destination, so and example could include airplane routes to different airports. Nodes are the different locations or points.  And arc is the path between each point. And a flow is what is being shipped across the arc.
